swERPSMIB.name: swERPSMIB
swERPSMIB.description: The MIB module for managing Ethernet Ring Protection Switching.

swERPSAdminState.name: swERPSAdminState
swERPSAdminState.description: This object indicates the ERPS state of the bridge.

swERPSLogState.name: swERPSLogState
swERPSLogState.description: This object indicates the ERPS log state of the bridge.

swERPSTrapState.name: swERPSTrapState
swERPSTrapState.description: This object indicates the ERPS trap state of the bridge.

swERPSMgmtRAPSVlanTable.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSVlanTable
swERPSMgmtRAPSVlanTable.description: This table contains the ERPS ring configuration information.

swERPSMgmtRAPSVlanEntry.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSVlanEntry
swERPSMgmtRAPSVlanEntry.description: A list of the ERPS ring configuration information.

swERPSMgmtRAPSVlanId.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSVlanId
swERPSMgmtRAPSVlanId.description: The RAPS VLAN is an index of the configuration.

swERPSMgmtRAPSWestPort.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSWestPort
swERPSMgmtRAPSWestPort.description: This is one of the RPL owner ports.The RPL owner may block this port. The value 0 indicates the west port is a virtual channel.

swERPSMgmtRAPSWestPortState.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSWestPortState
swERPSMgmtRAPSWestPortState.description: This is the west port state. The state may change occasionally. When the west port is configured on a virtual channel, the west port state is always forwarding.

swERPSMgmtRAPSEastPort.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSEastPort
swERPSMgmtRAPSEastPort.description: This is the other RPL owner port.The RPL Owner may block this port. The value 0 indicates the west port is a virtual channel.

swERPSMgmtRAPSEastPortState.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSEastPortState
swERPSMgmtRAPSEastPortState.description: This is the east port state. The state may change occasionally. When the east port is configured on a virtual channel, the east port state is always forwarding.

swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLPort.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLPort
swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLPort.description: When the port enable state is enabled, the RPL port's current port role is defined by the ERPS application.

swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerAdminState.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerAdminState
swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerAdminState.description: The administrative value of the RPL owner state. The RPL owner is an Ethernet Ring Node adjacent to the RPL that is responsible for blocking its end of the RPL under normal conditions.

swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlan.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlan
swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlan.description: The protection VLAN has prevented a loop.

swERPSMgmtRAPSRingMEL.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSRingMEL
swERPSMgmtRAPSRingMEL.description: The ring MEL is the maintenance entity group (MEG) level that provides a communication channel for the ring automatic protection switching (RAPS) information.

swERPSMgmtRAPSHoldOffTime.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSHoldOffTime
swERPSMgmtRAPSHoldOffTime.description: In order to coordinate the timing of protection switches at multiple layers.

swERPSMgmtRAPSGuardTime.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSGuardTime
swERPSMgmtRAPSGuardTime.description: This is used to prevent ring nodes from receiving outdated RAPS messages.

swERPSMgmtRAPSWTRTime.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSWTRTime
swERPSMgmtRAPSWTRTime.description: When revertive is enabled, this is used to prevent frequent operation of the protection switch due to an intermittent defect. A failed working transport entity must become stable in a fault-free state.

swERPSMgmtRAPSRingState.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSRingState
swERPSMgmtRAPSRingState.description: This indicates the state of the ring.The available states are: begin, init, idle, or protection.

swERPSMgmtRAPSRingAdminState.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSRingAdminState
swERPSMgmtRAPSRingAdminState.description: This indicates the administrative state of the ring.

swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperStatus.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperStatus
swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperStatus.description: The current operational value of the RPL owner state. The value 'active' is used to indicate that the RPL owner administrative state is enabled and the device is operating as the active RPL owner. The value 'inactive' is used to indicate that the RPL owner administrative state is enabled, but the device is operating as the inactive RPL owner. The value 'disabled' is used to indicate that the RPL owner administrative state of the device is disabled.

swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList1to.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList1to64
swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList1to.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1-512) that belong to the protected VLANs.

swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList65t.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList65to128
swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList65t.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (513-1024) that belong to the protected VLANs.

swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList129.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList129to192
swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList129.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1025-1536) that belong to the protected VLANs.

swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList193.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList193to256
swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList193.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1537-2048) that belong to the protected VLANs.

swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList257.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList257to320
swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList257.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (2049-2560) that belong to the protected VLANs.

swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList321.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList321to384
swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList321.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (2561-3072) that belongs to the protected VLANs.

swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList385.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList385to448
swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList385.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (3073-3584) that belong to the protected VLANs.

swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList449.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList449to512
swERPSMgmtRAPSProtectionVlanRangeList449.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (3585-4096) that belong to the protected VLANs.

swERPSMgmtRAPSRevertive.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSRevertive
swERPSMgmtRAPSRevertive.description: The object is used to enable or disable the revertive operation of a special ring. When revertive is disabled, the traffic link is allowed to use the RPL, after revovering from a failure. When revertive is enabled, the traffic link is restored to the working transport link.

swERPSMgmtRAPSOperWestPort.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSOperWestPort
swERPSMgmtRAPSOperWestPort.description: This object indicates actual running ring west port. The value 0 indicates the west port is a virtual channel.

swERPSMgmtRAPSOperEastPort.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSOperEastPort
swERPSMgmtRAPSOperEastPort.description: This object indicates actual running ring east port. The value 0 indicates the east port is a virtual channel.

swERPSMgmtRAPSOperRPLPort.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSOperRPLPort
swERPSMgmtRAPSOperRPLPort.description: This object indicates actual running ring RPL port.

swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperState.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperState
swERPSMgmtRAPSRPLOwnerOperState.description: This object indicates actual running RPL owner state.

swERPSMgmtRAPSRowStatus.name: swERPSMgmtRAPSRowStatus
swERPSMgmtRAPSRowStatus.description: This object indicates the RowStatus of this entry.

swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlTable.name: swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlTable
swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlTable.description: This table contains the ERPS sub-ring configuration information.

swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlEntry.name: swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlEntry
swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlEntry.description: A list of the ERPS sub-ring configuration information.

swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlRAPSVlanId.name: swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlRAPSVlanId
swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlRAPSVlanId.description: The RAPS VLAN is an index of the configuration.

swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlSubRingRAPSVlanId.name: swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlSubRingRAPSVlanId
swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlSubRingRAPSVlanId.description: This indicates the ring control VLAN-ID of the sub-ring which connects to another ring.

swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlTCPropagationState.name: swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlTCPropagationState
swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlTCPropagationState.description: This indicates the state of the sub-ring topology change propagation.

swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlRowStatus.name: swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlRowStatus
swERPSMgmtSubRingCtrlRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swERPSSFDetectedTrap.description: When a signal failure occurs, a trap will be generated.

swERPSSFClearedTrap.name: swERPSSFClearedTrap
swERPSSFClearedTrap.description: When the signal failure clears, a trap will be generated.
